The paper discusses an enriched extension of the theory of Rough Sets, which is a mathematical theory used in artificial intelligence and data mining. The paper also discusses the notion of linguistic variables, which are commonly used in information retrieval and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DM (Data Mining), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
